narrator:Todd Anderson walks nervously into the school newspaper office, clutching a stack of papers in his hands. He looks around, unsure of where to go. The other students in the office glance at him briefly before returning to their work.

Todd's face falls, and he stammers in response.

TODD:「B-but I didn't know, I'm sorry. Can't you make an exception?」

RACHEL:「Sorry, Anderson. The deadline is the deadline. We can't make exceptions for everyone.」

Todd's shoulders slump, and he begins to turn away, defeated. But then, he takes a deep breath and gathers his courage.

TODD:「I... I really worked hard on these articles. They're important to me. Is there anything I can do to get them in?」

RACHEL:「Alright, I'll make a deal with you. If you can get them edited and ready for print in the next half hour, I'll see if I can squeeze them in. But no promises.」

Todd's eyes light up with hope, and he nods eagerly.

TODD:「Thank you, thank you so much! I'll get right on it!」

As Todd rushes to find an available computer, the other students in the office watch him with curiosity and admiration. Todd's determination and willingness to go the extra mile are evident, even in the face of adversity.
